========================================================================
PART II: WHY ALL-ONES MAXIMIZES f₄ DESPITE MIXED SIGNS
========================================================================

For f₄(σ) to be maximized at all-ones, we need:
  For every σ ≠ all-ones:
    Σ_{S: χ_S(σ) = -1} ĥ[S] ≥ 0  (the "lost" positive + "gained" negative)

Equivalently: the positive ĥ[S] in the "flipped" set always outweigh
the negative ones.

Let's check this for each "neighboring" σ (differing from all-ones in
exactly one or two coordinates).


  p=13: f₄(all-ones) = 16891.8750

  Analysis of f₄ at all σ differing from all-ones:
    1 flips: max loss = 41678.0000 (worst: flip coords (0,))
    2 flips: max loss = 41678.0000 (worst: flip coords (1, 3))
    3 flips: max loss = 41678.0000 (worst: flip coords (0, 2, 3))
    4 flips: max loss = 41678.0000 (worst: flip coords (0, 1, 2, 4))
    5 flips: max loss = 41678.0000 (worst: flip coords (0, 1, 3, 4, 5))
    6 flips: max loss = 0 (all-ones ALWAYS better for 6 flips)

========================================================================
PART III: THE POSITIVE SUM DOMINANCE CONDITION
========================================================================

f₄(all-ones) = Σ_{S:|S|=4} ĥ[S]  (sum of all degree-4 coefficients)

For any σ: f₄(σ) = Σ_{S:|S|=4} ĥ[S] · χ_S(σ)

f₄(all-ones) - f₄(σ) = 2 · Σ_{S: χ_S(σ)=-1} ĥ[S]

So all-ones is the maximum iff for ALL σ:
  Σ_{S: χ_S(σ)=-1} ĥ[S] ≥ 0

This is a HYPERPLANE SEPARATION condition on the degree-4 coefficients!

For each σ, the set {S : χ_S(σ) = -1} is determined by the "parity"
structure of σ. Specifically, χ_S(σ) = -1 iff |S ∩ {flipped coords}| is odd.

If we flip coordinates in set F ⊂ {1,...,m}, then:
  {S : χ_S(σ)=-1} = {S : |S ∩ F| odd}

This is a LINEAR ALGEBRAIC condition on the 4-element subsets S.

  p=13: Checking hyperplane condition for all 2^m - 1 = 63 flip sets:

    Minimum hyperplane sum: 0.0000 at F=[1, 2, 3]
    ★★★ ALL HYPERPLANE SUMS ≥ 0! f₄ PROVED MAXIMIZED AT ALL-ONES! ★★★

========================================================================
PART IV: THE FULL H HYPERPLANE CONDITION
========================================================================

Now the BIG question: does the hyperplane condition hold for the FULL H,
not just the degree-4 part?

H(all-ones) - H(σ_F) = 2 · Σ_{S: |S∩F| odd} ĥ[S] ≥ 0 for all F?

This is the FULL condition for Interval maximality.


  p=7: min(H(all-ones) - H(σ)) = -14 at F=[1, 2]
    All-ones is NOT the maximum (deficit = -14)

  p=11: min(H(all-ones) - H(σ)) = -2068 at F=[2]
    All-ones is NOT the maximum (deficit = -2068)

  p=13: min(H(all-ones) - H(σ)) = 0 at F=[1, 2, 3]
    ★ All-ones IS the maximum!

